{"lemma":"مالِكٌ","slug":"مالِكٌ","root":"م.ل.ك","root_slug":"م-ل-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ل-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مالِك","root":"ملك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1094","n1095","n43703"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D9%83%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"owning, possessing, holding"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"owner"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Malik"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of مَلَكَ (malaka, “to own”)."},"ipa":["/maː.lik/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1094","headword_ar":"مَاْلَكٌ","root":"Alk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be the original form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An angel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because he conveys, or communicates, the message from God; (K, * TA, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA^k","text_ar":"لاك"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K, TA; [but in the CK is a mistake here, pointed out above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) so that the measure of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEalN","text_ar":"مَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is both sing. and pl.: Ks says that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olakN","text_ar":"مَاْلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “a message;” then, by transposition,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maloA^akN","text_ar":"مَلْاَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a form also in use; and then, in consequence of frequency of usage, the hemzeh is suppressed, so that it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but in forming the pl., they restore it to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maloA^akN","text_ar":"مَلْاَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAy^ikapN","text_ar":"مَلَايِكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAy^iku","text_ar":"مَلَايِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlk","text_ar":"ملك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or, accord. to some, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aka","text_ar":"لَاَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“he sent;” so that the measure of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafalN","text_ar":"مَفَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and there are other opinions respecting it: (Msb:) some say that its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a radical: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlk","text_ar":"ملك"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA^k","text_ar":"لاك"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n1095","headword_ar":"مَاْلُكٌ","root":"Alk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43703","headword_ar":"مَالِكٌ","root":"mlk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAliku AlA^amori","text_ar":"مَالِكُ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The possessor of command,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rule."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAliku Alkabiyru","text_ar":"المَالِكُ الكَبِيرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Great Master, or Owner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., God; in contradistinction to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAliku AlS~agiyru","text_ar":"المَالِكُ الصَّغِيرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the little master, or owner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., the human owner of a slave, &c. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlikN AlHaziynu","text_ar":"مَالِكٌ الحَزِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (so in one copy of the S: in another, and the MA, and Kzw,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAliku AlHaziyni","text_ar":"مَالِكُ الحَزِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a species thereof] in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwtymAr","text_ar":"بوتيمار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird, long in the neck and legs, called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwtymAr","text_ar":"بوتيمار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kzw:) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabayoTarN","text_ar":"سَبَيْطَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw maAlikK","text_ar":"اَبُو مَالِكٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbr","text_ar":"جبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abN","text_ar":"اَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Kzw"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}